               <ce:section-title>Abstract</ce:section-title>
               <ce:abstract-sec>
                  <ce:simple-para view="all" id="simple-para.0010">The RAM perturbation theory is evaluated in the case of the hard dumbbell fluid and compared with computer simulation results. The zeroth-order theory yields good agreement with the centres pair correlation function g<ce:inf loc="post">ooo</ce:inf> (<ce:italic>r</ce:italic>) even up to large dumbbell sphere separations, thus showing that the basic idea of the theory is sound. Some possible reasons for the failure of a related perturbation theory are discussed.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:abstract-sec>
            </ce:abstract>
